{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "02", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "13", "M": "44", "S": "52"}}, "news": [{"title": "How ULCRA held back Kolkata's growth and why its repeal could be a turning point for Bengal", "para": "Kolkata's urban growth faced decades of constraint due to the Urban Land (Ceiling and Regulation) Act, 1976. This law hindered large-scale development and investment. Now, the state government is considering its repeal. This move promises to unlock opportunities for real estate and infrastructure. It could simplify land acquisition and boost economic growth across West Bengal.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/blog/reforming-kolkata-the-impact-of-repealing-ulcra-on-urban-development/131460313?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-29210/131460313.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "reforming-kolkata-the-impact-of-repealing-ulcra-on-urban-development"}, {"title": "Chandigarh civic body nets record \u20b961 crore property tax in rebate window", "para": "Chandigarh's municipal corporation achieved a record Rs 61 crore in property tax during the April-May rebate period, surpassing last year's collection. Commercial properties contributed significantly, with residential units also showing strong participation. Taxpayers who missed the deadline now face a 25% penalty and 12% interest.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/chandigarh-municipal-corporation-records-highest-ever-61-crore-property-tax-collection-during-rebate-period/131461330?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-85486/131461330.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Uttarakhand HC extends stay on demolition of private properties for road widening in Haldwani", "para": "Uttarakhand High Court has extended its interim stay on demolishing private properties in Haldwani, halting a road-widening project. Petitioners, including hotel owners, claim demolition notices were issued with insufficient notice, violating procedures. They argue authorities are evicting them under the guise of removing encroachments without a fair hearing. The next hearing is scheduled for June 4.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/uttarakhand-high-court-halts-demolition-of-private-properties-in-haldwani-amid-road-widening-controversy/131461302?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-104674/131461302.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}